==English==
===Noun===

# {{Optics}} the [[law]] that, for a [[ray incident]] on the [[interface]] of two [[media]], the [[sine]] of the [[angle]] of [[incidence]] times the [[index]] of the [[refraction]] of the first [[medium]] is equal to the sine of the angle of refraction times the index of refraction of the second medium. [named after [[Willebrod Snell van Royen]] (d. 1626), Dutch [[mathematician]]